	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=1866#p1866">2011-01-22 05:10:06</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postbody">
				<div class="postleft">
					<dl>
						<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=92074">brugeman</a></strong></dt>
						<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					</dl>
				</div>
				<div class="postright">
					<h3>BT-radio, DHT extension</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>Hi. </p><p>I&#039;d like to propose a way to notify BT network about a new shared file. I&#039;ve seen 2 other topics (http://forum.bittorrent.org/viewtopic.php?id=139 , <a href="http://forum.bittorrent.org/viewtopic.php?id=110)">http://forum.bittorrent.org/viewtopic.php?id=110)</a> on content discovery, but proposed approach is quite different.</p><p>Not to waste you time, new BEP proposal: <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/torrent-radio/files/bep_34.txt/download">http://sourceforge.net/projects/torrent … t/download</a><br />Sample implementation based on DHT code by jch (from transmission 2.13): <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/torrent-radio/files/">http://sourceforge.net/projects/torrent-radio/files/</a></p><p>I&#039;d be happy to get any feedback. I&#039;m very new to BT internals, just starting to get involved, so please don&#039;t judge too hard. At least I hope you&#039;ll like the core idea.</p><p>Also, my implementation wasn&#039;t given any testing, so it&#039;s rather a starting point than a working thing.<br />And sorry for my english, just in case.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postfoot clearb">
